The paper deals with lower bounds for graph embedding problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms, computational geometry, and combinatorics. The introduction of new combinatorial problems and the use of the Exponential Time Hypothesis suggest a connection to computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
